WEBVTT

00:07.608 --> 00:10.744
Snake Doc, decoy's off.

00:10.811 --> 00:14.115
[ Jonas On Radio ]
Roger that.
See you at the R.V.

00:15.216 --> 00:17.151
What do you mean,
I have the horse?

00:17.218 --> 00:21.389
His owner, Chief Haji,
told the groom's envoy you have
the horse Sahar must ride.

00:21.455 --> 00:23.524
For the marriage
to take place,

00:23.591 --> 00:26.060
Sahar must arrive on
her father's championship
Buzkashi horse.

00:26.127 --> 00:29.530
Our job is to deliver the bride
to the groom's village, period!

00:29.597 --> 00:32.700
Nobody said anything
about a horse!

00:32.766 --> 00:36.604
Your government work hard
to broker peace
between the Kom and the Gujjar.

00:36.670 --> 00:38.539
You want a truce or not?

00:40.141 --> 00:42.176
What's the holdup?

00:42.243 --> 00:44.078
Seems we're short
of some transportation.

00:44.145 --> 00:47.047
Nah. Still here.

00:47.115 --> 00:49.517
No. We're talking about
a horse.

00:49.583 --> 00:52.620
Look, we got about 10 hours
to get to the groom's village...

00:52.686 --> 00:54.955
before the Taliban
gets hip to our decoy,

00:55.022 --> 00:58.492
and the only way to make it
that fast in this terrain
is in the Land Rover.

00:58.559 --> 01:01.895
If you want the truce to stand,
this marriage between
the two tribes must take place.

01:01.962 --> 01:06.934
For the marriage to take place,
Sahar must arrive
on her father's Buzkashi horse.

01:07.000 --> 01:09.437
This is tradition.
Cannot be violated.

01:11.872 --> 01:13.707
[ Exhales ]

01:17.745 --> 01:19.880
All right.

01:19.947 --> 01:22.950
Her father's horse--
Where is it?

01:23.016 --> 01:26.754
He lost it--
two days ago, in wager.

01:26.820 --> 01:31.091
Groom's representative,
his envoy, is here to make sure
all protocol is correct.

01:31.159 --> 01:33.627
He cannot learn
the horse is gone.

01:33.694 --> 01:36.897
- And you want us
to get the horse?
- You must get the horse.

01:36.964 --> 01:39.300
Where is it?

01:39.367 --> 01:43.437
[ Shouting, Cheering ]

01:43.504 --> 01:45.473
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

01:59.620 --> 02:02.923
I should've
stayed in dental college.

02:02.990 --> 02:06.427
State Department is relying
on our well-honed
diplomatic skill.

02:06.494 --> 02:10.531
I really don't want to die
for some horse.

02:10.598 --> 02:13.234
Well, we gotta buy it
before we die for it.

02:13.301 --> 02:16.937
- How much you got?
- 60,000 bukars.

02:17.004 --> 02:20.073
I got 80,000.
Should be enough.

02:20.140 --> 02:22.142
Betty Blue, stand by.

02:41.729 --> 02:44.265
Well, where's
the nearest A.T.M.?

02:45.599 --> 02:48.269
Betty Blue, I need you now.

03:00.448 --> 03:04.285
- [ Laughs ]
- [ Laughing ]

03:13.093 --> 03:14.828
[ Horse Whinnies ]
[ Jonas ]
Yeah.

03:28.075 --> 03:31.745
Uh-huh.
Let's go get our horses.

03:34.482 --> 03:38.986
We've had a breakthrough
thanks to Kim
and Ms. Blane.

03:39.052 --> 03:42.523
Seems Kim's new employer
is our new person
of interest.

03:42.590 --> 03:45.092
- Isaac Reed.
- Yeah.

03:45.158 --> 03:47.060
Documents she found
in his office.

03:47.127 --> 03:50.230
Reed has the routing and
account numbers for three
U.S. banks and one in Dubai.

03:50.298 --> 03:52.065
He's the money launderer
for the terrorists.

03:52.132 --> 03:54.935
So he was involved
with the assassinations?
We believe so.

03:55.002 --> 03:56.904
I want Kim out of that house.

03:56.970 --> 04:00.374
It's vital we maintain
the link to Isaac Reed,
and right now, that's Kim.

04:00.441 --> 04:03.344
So let's figure out
how she can help you
get inside.

04:04.678 --> 04:08.349
[ Chattering ]
So Kim said
to the other mother,

04:08.416 --> 04:10.451
"When your child
stops licking the walls,

04:10.518 --> 04:12.353
I'll heed your advice
and take away
Ella's pacifier."

04:12.420 --> 04:14.555
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Laughs ]

04:14.622 --> 04:17.958
Oh. Your wife
is a godsend, Bob.
Well--

04:18.025 --> 04:20.561
What can I say?
I'm smitten with your child.

04:20.628 --> 04:23.464
- [ Exhales ]
Ah, I got this one.
- No, no, no. Let me.

04:23.531 --> 04:25.299
- I insist. It's on me.
- You sure?

04:25.366 --> 04:27.501
Yeah. Look at that.

04:31.305 --> 04:33.173
Thanks so much.
Sure.

04:33.240 --> 04:36.810
So Kim tells me
you want to talk business.
Yes, that's right.

04:36.877 --> 04:39.813
How is AeroDyne Alliance?
Sales have doubled
in sunny California.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.782
Not that I see much of it,
doing international sales.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.617
Be nice if you were home
more often.

04:43.684 --> 04:45.653
But then who'd pay for your
shoes and dresses, darling?

04:45.719 --> 04:48.021
Our big problem
at the moment...

04:48.088 --> 04:50.724
is that our leather importer
has been dropping
the ball lately.

04:50.791 --> 04:53.527
It's delayed 30%
of our orders.
That's not good.

04:53.594 --> 04:57.365
No. In a white glove business
like ours, it's a disaster.
We're looking for someone new.

04:57.431 --> 04:59.367
I might be able
to help you out.

04:59.433 --> 05:01.902
I'll take all the help
I can get.

05:01.969 --> 05:04.037
I'm sorry, sir,
but your credit card
was declined.

05:04.104 --> 05:07.675
[ Scoffs ]
Just run it again, huh?
Sir, we did.

05:07.741 --> 05:09.877
- That's not right.
Let me make a call.
- [ Kim ] Bob--

05:09.943 --> 05:13.447
Guys, why don't you
let me get this one?
You can get the next one.

05:13.514 --> 05:15.816
Please. Please. Here.
That should cover it.

05:15.883 --> 05:19.186
[ Waiter ] Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]
This is embarrassing.

05:19.252 --> 05:22.390
- No, it happens to us all.
- I'm done with this card.

05:22.456 --> 05:24.792
I'm gonna cancel it right now.
Kim, you ready to go?

05:26.093 --> 05:28.028
[ Zipper Closes ]

05:28.095 --> 05:30.998
Isaac, nice to meet you.
Oh, it's a pleasure.

05:31.064 --> 05:32.933
All right. Let's go.

05:37.070 --> 05:39.873
[ Whinnies ]

05:41.442 --> 05:44.011
[ Horse Nickers ]

05:44.077 --> 05:45.879
Saddle up, Red Ryder.

05:49.116 --> 05:51.051
[ Jonas ]
Need some help there, soldier?
I got it.

05:51.118 --> 05:53.621
You've always remarked
it's the pointless missions...

05:53.687 --> 05:55.589
that get you
the bullet in the back.

05:55.656 --> 05:57.691
Mm-hmm.
[ Whinnies ]

05:59.159 --> 06:01.795
[ Grunts ]

06:01.862 --> 06:03.797
Have I told you
I don't really like horses?

06:03.864 --> 06:06.266
Well, cheer up.
We're going to a wedding.

06:06.333 --> 06:08.436
Hyah!

06:09.437 --> 06:11.338
[ Whinnies ]

06:11.405 --> 06:15.075
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

06:15.142 --> 06:19.079
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

06:19.146 --> 06:21.649
* See another dawn *

06:21.715 --> 06:23.584
* Through a daughter's eyes *

06:23.651 --> 06:27.988
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

06:36.029 --> 06:37.965
Does it bother you
sending a little girl off...

06:38.031 --> 06:40.734
to marry a 40-year-old
with two wives already?

06:40.801 --> 06:42.903
It would
if I thought about it.

06:42.970 --> 06:45.338
Bother you, Carlo?

06:45.405 --> 06:49.510
Dude, who are we
to meddle in the cultures
of this ancient land?

06:57.485 --> 07:01.855
The groom must be
very excited to marry
such a young and pretty bride.

07:01.922 --> 07:05.192
Sahar is fortunate.
This marriage will
elevate her status.

07:05.258 --> 07:08.796
- Her father is not
who he seems to be.
- Is that so?

07:08.862 --> 07:12.533
I'm fully aware the stallion
she rides was purchased by you
and the American government.

07:12.600 --> 07:14.502
It doesn't belong to Chief Haji.

07:14.568 --> 07:18.171
This means he does not have
the power or stature
he would have others believe.

07:18.238 --> 07:21.441
Such would be grounds
for my chief to cancel
the marriage contract.

07:21.509 --> 07:23.511
Well, I trust
it won't come to that.

07:23.577 --> 07:25.479
The truce is unprecedented.

07:25.546 --> 07:28.516
You desire it
because my chief will prevent
attacks on your soldiers.

07:28.582 --> 07:31.885
I, because it is
the first step toward peace
in these mountains.

07:31.952 --> 07:34.387
So I'm very much
in favor of the truce.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.624
At what price?

07:36.690 --> 07:39.059
A small one--
a million Afghani.

07:39.126 --> 07:41.161
Well, that's a lot of money.

07:41.228 --> 07:44.898
My chief will have no reason
to learn of the misfortunes
of Sahar's father...

07:44.965 --> 07:47.868
or the true
owner of that horse.
Aha.

07:47.935 --> 07:50.437
And he will throw in
an Al-Qaeda lieutenant.

07:50.504 --> 07:52.740
Sold.

08:05.352 --> 08:07.721
I know.
Rocks, my 6:00.

08:07.788 --> 08:09.823
[ Mack ]
I'm on it.

08:40.921 --> 08:43.090
Who are you?

08:43.156 --> 08:46.794
You speak English.
Oh, thank God.

08:46.860 --> 08:50.063
You are American?
No. I'm Dutch.

08:50.130 --> 08:54.602
I'm an aid worker
with World Relief Project.

08:54.668 --> 08:56.937
My name is Lara Beerson.

08:57.004 --> 08:58.939
May I--
May I have some water?

08:59.006 --> 09:03.577
- [ Panting ]
- Easy. Easy now.

09:03.644 --> 09:05.879
Not so much.
[ Coughs ]

09:08.616 --> 09:11.619
I've been working
in a Taku village.

09:11.685 --> 09:15.522
My partner and I
went to get supplies,
and we were attacked by bandits.

09:15.589 --> 09:20.127
They killed him,
and I escaped.

09:20.193 --> 09:25.065
I've been without food and water
for two days.

09:27.567 --> 09:29.903
Oh, thank you.

09:32.940 --> 09:36.276
May I ask who you are?
We're fellow wayfarers.

09:39.079 --> 09:42.883
Please join us.
We'll get you to safety.

09:42.950 --> 09:44.952
Get her some food.
Thank you.

09:49.456 --> 09:51.424
She will slow us down.

09:51.491 --> 09:54.728
And what if she's captured
and gives away our position?

09:54.795 --> 09:56.964
Better to have a guest
than a hostile witness.

10:08.809 --> 10:12.312
Kim?
What are you doing here?
I forgot I had Bobo.

10:12.379 --> 10:15.348
I put him in my bag yesterday
when I took Ella to the park.

10:15.415 --> 10:17.617
- She won't sleep without him.
- Ah, thanks.

10:17.685 --> 10:21.321
Hey, it's not much of a day off
when you have to see me twice.

10:22.823 --> 10:27.360
I-I also wanted to apologize
for my husband's behavior.

10:27.427 --> 10:30.397
He's under a lot of stress.
[ Phone Ringing ]

10:30.463 --> 10:32.700
Excuse me.

10:34.101 --> 10:36.136
[ Ringing Stops ]
I'm sorry.

10:36.203 --> 10:38.271
You were saying
your husband was under
a lot of stress?

10:38.338 --> 10:42.375
- ...take your call right now,
but we'll get back to you--
- You could say it's financial.

10:42.442 --> 10:46.346
[ Machine Beeps ]
Mr. Reed.
This is Joe Landers.

10:46.413 --> 10:50.751
- I'm still looking for Noelle.
I know she works there--
- [ Beeps ]

10:52.720 --> 10:54.755
You're busy.
I should get going.

10:54.822 --> 10:57.324
No. It's not important.
Stay.

10:57.390 --> 11:01.661
So, what kind
of financial problems
is Bob having?

11:01.729 --> 11:03.630
Look,
I shouldn't have said anything.

11:03.697 --> 11:06.233
I'll see you tomorrow.
Kim, please.

11:06.299 --> 11:08.769
Tell me what's wrong.

11:11.805 --> 11:15.008
Bob and I, we're--

11:17.778 --> 11:19.747
God. Uh--

11:19.813 --> 11:24.918
I believe the phrase is,
"having a hard time
making ends meet."

11:24.985 --> 11:28.388
Isn't AeroDyne
taking care of Bob?
It isn't AeroDyne.

11:28.455 --> 11:30.523
Well, what is it then?

11:30.590 --> 11:32.425
Bob likes to bet on sports.

11:35.095 --> 11:39.032
He's having a hard time now--
has been, for a while.

11:40.868 --> 11:42.970
And that's why
you have a job as a nanny?

11:43.036 --> 11:46.073
Don't get me wrong.
I love kids.

11:47.440 --> 11:50.410
I'm gonna go,
before I start crying
in front of you.

11:50.477 --> 11:55.148
You stay here with Ella.
Hey, let me see
what I can do to help.

12:04.792 --> 12:06.794
- [ Giggles ]
- [ Chuckles ]

12:09.729 --> 12:11.799
She likes you.

12:13.633 --> 12:15.903
Think her fiancÃ©
would approve?

12:22.609 --> 12:26.880
How does she fit into our cover
as a Wakhi trading caravan?

12:26.947 --> 12:31.084
We're Good Wakhi Samaritans--
saving a stranded woman.

12:31.151 --> 12:34.121
We'd better get more
than an Al-Qaeda lieutenant
by the time this trip's over.

12:40.961 --> 12:43.563
He says Arif stole
the white horse's jewelry.

12:43.630 --> 12:46.399
It's in his saddlebag.

12:48.501 --> 12:53.073
You see? You see? He's a thief.
That is Zar's
championship prize.

12:53.140 --> 12:55.742
It was planted--
by him or the woman.

12:55.809 --> 12:57.845
- I'll kill you.
- No, you won't,

12:57.911 --> 13:00.513
because the wedding
would be off
and then the truce would be off.

13:02.182 --> 13:04.952
Here. Take it back.
The chief will be proud
of your vigilance.

13:05.018 --> 13:08.421
I don't want any more fighting
out of you two. Understood?

13:13.827 --> 13:16.796
Get some rest.
We ride at dawn.

13:16.864 --> 13:20.600
Wait. I need to talk to you
about something.

13:20.667 --> 13:24.304
- [ Gasps ]
- [ Gurgling ]

13:28.241 --> 13:29.276
[ Gasps ]

13:35.015 --> 13:38.051
He would have killed me
in my sleep.

13:39.452 --> 13:41.321
We need him alive.

13:48.962 --> 13:51.531
Get some rest.

13:51.598 --> 13:54.734
He left here half an hour ago.
He should be there already.

13:54.801 --> 13:57.604
Maybe he's not coming.

13:57.670 --> 14:00.908
Yeah. Look, I gotta go.
You, uh-- You get back
to your job, okay? Bye.

14:00.974 --> 14:03.043
[ Inhales ]

14:04.311 --> 14:06.346
This is
a pleasant surprise.
Bob.

14:06.413 --> 14:08.415
How you doing?

14:08.481 --> 14:12.352
Bob, your wife
told me everything.
What did Kim tell you?

14:12.419 --> 14:17.257
That you have a little habit
that's bleeding you both dry.

14:17.324 --> 14:20.460
- Look, the problem
is in her head--
- How much do you owe, Bob?

14:21.929 --> 14:23.897
Who the hell
do you think you are?

14:23.964 --> 14:25.632
Bob, I'm your fairy godmother.
That's who I am.

14:28.101 --> 14:30.437
I have a client,
a very wealthy client,

14:30.503 --> 14:32.839
who has a private plane
that's hangared locally.

14:32.906 --> 14:37.210
He needs some upgrades
made to it--
carpet, seats, panel lights.

14:37.277 --> 14:39.846
'Bout 200 thou worth of work,
but he's willing
to pay 800 thou.

14:39.913 --> 14:42.249
Hmm.
What's the catch?

14:42.315 --> 14:46.853
He wants absolute anonymity--
no names, no questions asked.
You deal only with me.

14:46.920 --> 14:51.391
Plus, you'll have to deliver
the plane in 48 hours
to Las Vegas, personally.

14:51.458 --> 14:54.527
[ Chuckles ]
And for that, he's willing
to pay a 400% markup?

14:54.594 --> 14:56.563
As soon as the plane
is delivered,

14:56.629 --> 14:58.698
the money will be wired into
your company's sales account.

14:58.765 --> 15:03.336
I'll take 50% for my fee,
you'll have 10%
for your troubles,

15:03.403 --> 15:05.338
and the rest
will go to AeroDyne Alliance,

15:05.405 --> 15:08.441
who'll make a nice
big fat profit on the job.

15:08.508 --> 15:11.711
- And everyone
comes out happier.
- And it's all perfectly legal.

15:11.778 --> 15:14.514
The only thing unorthodox
is you won't be able
to talk about it.

15:14.581 --> 15:16.416
Why me?

15:18.418 --> 15:21.421
My daughter's grown
very fond of your wife, Bob.

15:21.488 --> 15:24.357
She's like family to us,
and I don't like
to see her upset.

15:24.424 --> 15:27.160
Maybe I don't like you
showing such concern
for my wife.

15:27.227 --> 15:29.262
Maybe she should stop
working for you.

15:29.329 --> 15:33.100
There are very few
golden opportunities
in life, Bob.

15:33.166 --> 15:35.168
I'm offering you one.
Would you like it?

15:39.539 --> 15:41.841
[ Exhales ]
Yes.

15:41.908 --> 15:46.413
- What?
- Yes. Yes.

15:49.849 --> 15:53.720
Here's 15,000 for your time.
Consider it a consultation fee.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.158
Is there anything else
you'd like to say to me?

16:00.227 --> 16:04.164
Thank you.
My pleasure.

16:07.600 --> 16:10.237
I know who you are
and why you're here.

16:10.303 --> 16:12.705
The girls
told me everything.
[ Scoffs ]

16:12.772 --> 16:15.675
You're actually delivering
a 12-year-old child
into a marriage?

16:15.742 --> 16:17.544
Well, that's news to me.

16:17.610 --> 16:19.712
You're supposed to help
these people.

16:19.779 --> 16:22.849
How can you perpetuate
this barbaric practice?

16:22.915 --> 16:25.418
Listen, miss.
I'm just a driver.

16:28.055 --> 16:30.690
Do you have children?
Daughters?

16:32.092 --> 16:35.062
I don't believe
you can all be so heartless.
[ Radio Beeping ]

16:38.931 --> 16:42.402
- [ Beeps ]
- [ Man ] Snake Doctor,
this is Kilo Two Bravo.

16:42.469 --> 16:44.571
Kilo Two Bravo,
this is Snake Doc.

16:44.637 --> 16:48.441
We just received word
that the decoy convoy
was attacked by Taliban forces.

16:48.508 --> 16:51.478
Any casualties?
Two soldiers wounded.

16:51.544 --> 16:54.781
Did the cover hold?
Negative. They realized
that it was a decoy bride.

16:54.847 --> 16:59.752
- They moved off
into your direction.
- Roger that. Snake Doc out.

17:03.690 --> 17:06.393
Throw the babies to the wolves.
We're traveling light and fast.

17:22.142 --> 17:24.577
[ Mack ]
We gotta rest
these horses soon.

17:24.644 --> 17:26.813
At this rate,
we're gonna run 'em
into the ground.

17:26.879 --> 17:31.084
No. We need cover,
and we need to ride
until we find some.

17:31.151 --> 17:33.586
[ Sahar Screams ]
[ Horse Grunting ]

17:41.294 --> 17:44.897
- What happened?
- Hard to say.
Exhaustion, maybe.

17:44.964 --> 17:48.368
Then this is not the
Buzkashi champion that played
for 10 hours without a break.

17:48.435 --> 17:51.971
I grew up with horses.
There's red around his eyes,

17:52.038 --> 17:54.006
and he has discharge
from his nostrils.

17:54.073 --> 17:56.976
He has an infection.

17:57.043 --> 18:00.180
[ Grunting Continues ]

18:03.850 --> 18:05.652
Let's get you up, Zar.

18:05.718 --> 18:09.756
He needs a vet.
I've seen this before.

18:09.822 --> 18:13.025
[ Mack ]
Easy now.

18:13.092 --> 18:15.128
There you go.

18:15.195 --> 18:18.931
- Where's the nearest village?
- Uh, Omari.

18:18.998 --> 18:21.868
Uh, I know of
the horse doctor there,
but it's a Taliban village.

18:21.934 --> 18:24.304
Well, what can
go wrong there?

18:24.371 --> 18:27.507
- Can this horse walk?
- Not with any weight on him.

18:27.574 --> 18:30.410
You aren't seriously thinking
of going to Omari?

18:30.477 --> 18:32.812
This horse dies,
the wedding's canceled?

18:32.879 --> 18:35.582
- Yes.
- Off we go.

18:40.052 --> 18:42.589
Well, then,
should've stayed
in dental school.

18:56.736 --> 18:59.339
[ Horse Whinnies ]

19:15.555 --> 19:20.227
You're not Dutch. You behave
more like American soldiers.

19:25.498 --> 19:27.900
[ Mack ]
We've spent time
with the Americans.

19:27.967 --> 19:30.437
Perhaps some of their ways
have rubbed off on us,

19:31.471 --> 19:33.906
such as their generosity
with whiskey.

19:35.942 --> 19:38.678
It's yours if you want it.

19:45.485 --> 19:49.622
- You're not Taliban.
- I am Pashtun.

19:51.758 --> 19:55.495
Where are these Americans now?
Help us,
and we will tell you.

19:55.562 --> 19:57.430
You should know that
the men in this village...

19:57.497 --> 20:01.601
are looking for a group
of American soldiers
traveling with a bridal party.

20:01.668 --> 20:04.304
Your horse
has a serious infection.

20:08.408 --> 20:11.344
Leave your horse.
Come back at nightfall.

20:11.411 --> 20:13.346
[ Jonas ]
And what if
we prefer to wait?

20:13.413 --> 20:15.848
Go, if you want
your horse to live.

20:15.915 --> 20:20.320
If you're successful,
you will be well rewarded--
very well.

20:29.362 --> 20:32.732
[ Knocking ]
Excuse me.
Is this Joe Landers?

20:32.799 --> 20:37.169
Joe, there's someone
here to see you.

20:37.236 --> 20:40.940
Hi. My name is Lisa.

20:41.007 --> 20:45.512
I think you might know
someone I know.
His name is Isaac Reed.

20:45.578 --> 20:51.484
He's kept this here for months,
but he can't remember who it is
because of his Alzheimer's.

20:58.791 --> 21:00.693
Joe.

21:02.228 --> 21:05.097
Joe?

21:05.164 --> 21:08.635
Did you call this number
yesterday and leave a message?

21:12.271 --> 21:15.141
I don't know.
Who's Noelle?

21:15.207 --> 21:18.678
I believe it's his daughter.
He's mentioned her before.

21:18.745 --> 21:21.047
She hasn't returned
my phone calls.

21:21.113 --> 21:23.416
But I know she lives
with that man. She's his nanny.

21:23.483 --> 21:26.519
She's Isaac Reed's nanny?
Yes.

21:26.586 --> 21:29.121
Noelle is Mr. Reed's nanny.

21:29.188 --> 21:33.526
She used to call me
all the time,
but she doesn't now.

21:33.593 --> 21:35.695
I mean, it's been weeks.

21:35.762 --> 21:40.166
I can tell you that Noelle
isn't Mr. Reed's nanny anymore.
She left.

21:40.232 --> 21:42.068
Why would she leave
without telling me?

21:43.470 --> 21:46.639
Did you, uh,
report her as missing?

21:46.706 --> 21:52.044
I talked to a policeman. I--
He said I was confused and--

21:56.883 --> 22:01.454
Noelle, you haven't
gotten yourself
into trouble again?

22:01.521 --> 22:04.824
Pardon?
Did that Mr. Reed
get you pregnant, huh?

22:04.891 --> 22:06.859
You should go now.
He's sundowning.

22:06.926 --> 22:08.695
What?
It's okay.
He gets more confused...

22:08.761 --> 22:11.564
and paranoid
at the end of the day.
But you're not Noelle.

22:11.631 --> 22:13.666
It's okay.
No, no.
You're not Noelle.

22:13.733 --> 22:17.236
- Please leave now.
- What have--
What have you done with her?

22:17.303 --> 22:19.706
[ Woman ]
It's okay. It's okay.

22:21.541 --> 22:25.344
This horse has the lines
of a Buzkashi champion.

22:25.412 --> 22:27.447
He must rest overnight.

22:27.514 --> 22:32.885
- Come. I have food and drink.
- We don't have time.
Is the horse good to go?

22:32.952 --> 22:35.888
It is a grave insult
to refuse Pashtun hospitality.

22:35.955 --> 22:39.091
And if you take the horse now,
you will kill him.

22:42.729 --> 22:46.065
This Kabul water is excellent,
don't you think?

22:48.735 --> 22:52.705
Mmm! This is the first water
I've had that was 80 proof.

22:52.772 --> 22:54.774
[ Mack ]
But we should pay you...

22:54.841 --> 22:58.678
and not take advantage
of your wonderful hospitality.

22:58.745 --> 23:00.713
Later.

23:00.780 --> 23:03.716
My friends want to know
about these Americans
you came across.

23:04.984 --> 23:07.620
Well, there were
six soldiers in uniform,

23:07.687 --> 23:09.689
and they drove
a mountain vehicle.

23:09.756 --> 23:11.624
Where?

23:12.825 --> 23:14.727
[ Both Grunt ]

23:29.141 --> 23:31.110
[ Switches Clicking ]

23:31.177 --> 23:34.046
[ Cell Phone Rings ]
[ Beeps ]

23:34.113 --> 23:37.049
Bob Cahill.
[ Isaac ] You ready, Bob?
Let's make this happen.

23:37.116 --> 23:39.018
Ready to go.

23:39.085 --> 23:42.221
Okay. Set a heading
for Henderson Airport
in Las Vegas.

23:42.288 --> 23:45.391
About 30 minutes out,
you'll be contacted
by my Las Vegas associate,

23:45.458 --> 23:47.460
Leon Drake
at air link support.

23:47.527 --> 23:49.729
He'll give you very specific
landing instructions.

23:49.796 --> 23:51.798
Do not speak to anyone but Leon.

23:51.864 --> 23:57.103
He'll confirm his identity
by saying, "The gray whales
were migrating to Mexico."

23:57.169 --> 23:59.371
"The gray whales
were migrating to Mexico."
Got it.

23:59.438 --> 24:02.208
Exactly. If he doesn't say it,
cease all communication
and return to California.

24:02.274 --> 24:03.876
You understand?

24:03.943 --> 24:06.112
Yes.
You know, Bob,
if this works out,

24:06.178 --> 24:08.347
we'll have a lot more
work together in the future.

24:08.414 --> 24:10.249
Your financial problems
will be over.

24:10.316 --> 24:13.285
Very good.
[ Beeps ]

24:13.352 --> 24:16.956
These are Noelle's keys.
I found them in Reed's desk.

24:17.023 --> 24:19.125
I think
something happened to her.

24:19.191 --> 24:22.495
Her father spoke to the police.
They ignored him
because he has Alzheimer's.

24:22.562 --> 24:24.731
Doesn't mean he can't have
moments of clarity.

24:24.797 --> 24:27.967
What's Reed said about her?
Nothing.

24:28.034 --> 24:30.837
Just that
she quit without warning
right before I started.

24:30.903 --> 24:34.340
- Can you handle this?
- I think so, yes.

24:34.406 --> 24:36.876
Good.

24:36.943 --> 24:39.679
In the meantime,
let me try to find
Noelle Landers's whereabouts.

24:42.949 --> 24:46.619
[ Man On Radio ]
Gulf Sierra 242, this is
air link support. Come in.

24:46.686 --> 24:49.055
This is Gulf Sierra 242.
Over.

24:49.121 --> 24:51.090
Bob, it's Leon Drake.

24:51.157 --> 24:55.562
We met before in Cabo,
around the time the gray whales
were migrating to Mexico?

24:56.529 --> 24:58.430
I remember. Go ahead.

24:58.497 --> 25:02.068
I'm sure Isaac gave you
a heads-up. Here's what
I want you to do, Bob.

25:02.134 --> 25:06.606
Drop down to 9,000 feet,
set a course 20 degrees
due north.

25:08.274 --> 25:10.509
That'll put me out of range
for Henderson Airport.

25:10.577 --> 25:14.213
There's been a change of plans.
You're not landing at Henderson.

25:14.280 --> 25:16.983
All right.
Where am I landing?

25:26.425 --> 25:28.861
[ Switches Clicking ]

25:31.330 --> 25:32.799
[ Siren Whoops ]

25:32.865 --> 25:34.867
[ Man On Megaphone ]
This is the F.B.I.

25:34.934 --> 25:37.604
Step out of the plane
with your hands in the air.

25:39.238 --> 25:41.641
[ Groans ]

25:48.180 --> 25:50.883
Up. Come on.
Wake up.

25:59.826 --> 26:02.862
[ Rooster Crows ]

26:02.929 --> 26:05.665
They stole the damn horse!

26:08.100 --> 26:10.036
Oh, that hurt.

26:18.544 --> 26:20.512
[ Door Closes ]

26:20.579 --> 26:25.284
[ Exhales ]
Okay, you know what?

26:28.320 --> 26:30.422
- Hello, Bob.
- Leon Drake.

26:30.489 --> 26:35.728
Actually, it's not, but that's
how Isaac Reed knows me.
[ Folder Hits Table ]

26:35.795 --> 26:38.197
- So you work for Reed.
- No.

26:38.264 --> 26:40.667
No? Reed didn't send you
on this joyride?

26:40.733 --> 26:42.669
No. I work
for AeroDyne Alliance.

26:42.735 --> 26:47.139
I'm delivering a customized
plane that Reed ordered.
What's this all about?

26:47.206 --> 26:49.275
The F.B.I.
has reason to believe...

26:49.341 --> 26:51.844
that Reed and his associates
may be involved
in illegal activity.

26:51.911 --> 26:55.682
We've been investigating him
for over a year.
And what have you discovered?

26:55.748 --> 26:59.351
Hmm.
Bob Cahill.

26:59.418 --> 27:04.924
Married, no children. Sales
executive for AeroDyne Alliance
for the last five years.

27:04.991 --> 27:08.527
The company relocated
from Kansas a few months back.

27:08.594 --> 27:10.496
But here's the really
interesting thing.

27:10.562 --> 27:13.866
AeroDyne Alliance
has been in business
for 20 years,

27:13.933 --> 27:17.970
and yet no one I talk to
has ever done business
with it.

27:19.672 --> 27:21.974
Who exactly are you, Bob?

27:27.213 --> 27:31.884
You're in over your head
or AeroDyne Alliance
is a C.I.A. front.

27:31.951 --> 27:34.253
You work
for the government, Bob?

27:35.554 --> 27:38.524
'Cause if you do, the good news
is we're on the same team.

27:38.590 --> 27:42.661
You come clean now, we can still
have a couple drinks in the
Hurricane Bar before last call.

27:42.729 --> 27:45.865
Okay. Okay.
I work for AeroDyne Alliance.

27:45.932 --> 27:48.801
We customize private planes,
from interiors to engines--

27:48.868 --> 27:51.237
How well do you know
Isaac Reed?
I don't.

27:51.303 --> 27:53.605
You don't know him?
I don't know him well.

27:53.672 --> 27:56.909
- He's a customer who placed
an order. That's all I know.
- So this plane is his?

27:56.976 --> 27:58.845
I don't know.
He placed an order.

27:58.911 --> 28:01.513
As long as he pays his bills,
that's all my company's
concerned with.

28:01.580 --> 28:04.183
- How much is he paying you?
- I'm not at liberty to say.

28:04.250 --> 28:06.418
Discretion and confidentiality
are cornerstones
of this business.

28:06.485 --> 28:10.156
So you don't care who you
do business with as long as
they pay their bills?

28:10.222 --> 28:12.591
Oh, come on.
Do you know another definition
of capitalism?

28:12.658 --> 28:14.426
Look, I may not work
for the government,

28:14.493 --> 28:17.496
but I know that you
have no legal authority
to hold me here.

28:17.563 --> 28:20.900
You have no flight plan
on record, and I'm the
only one who knows you're here.

28:20.967 --> 28:23.035
You think your pal Reed's
gonna bail you out?

28:23.102 --> 28:26.405
Cancel your plans, Bob.
You're in for a long night.

28:30.576 --> 28:34.180
Horse is in the village,
behind the mullah's house.

28:34.246 --> 28:36.515
He's got six armed guards
surrounding the place.

28:36.582 --> 28:38.885
If we take him by force,
the horse might get injured.

28:38.951 --> 28:40.887
Well, then, we don't
take him by force.

28:40.953 --> 28:43.089
We need your help.

28:43.155 --> 28:45.892
I don't approve
of anything that leads
to an underage marriage,

28:45.958 --> 28:48.627
to what is, in effect,
the sale of a young girl.

28:48.694 --> 28:50.629
Listen to me.

28:50.696 --> 28:54.600
When we get the horse back,
we'll listen to your objections.
All right?

28:54.666 --> 28:58.905
[ Sighs ]
All right.

29:00.907 --> 29:03.475
[ Jonas ]
You'll need these.

29:06.578 --> 29:08.848
What's your plan?

29:10.182 --> 29:12.751
Hmm.
Watch and be amazed.

29:25.497 --> 29:27.333
You stole my horse.

29:27.399 --> 29:31.303
I had no choice.
The mullah demanded it.

29:31.370 --> 29:34.640
You're lucky
I didn't give them enough
tranquilizers to kill you.

29:34.706 --> 29:37.409
- Now you're gonna help me
get it back.
- What shall I do?

29:37.476 --> 29:41.513
The first thing we'll need
is rat poison.

29:49.688 --> 29:51.690
[ Horse Whinnies ]

29:51.757 --> 29:54.793
[ Chattering
In Foreign Language ]

29:58.264 --> 30:02.001
[ Bird Cawing ]

30:30.529 --> 30:32.431
Very good.

30:57.389 --> 30:59.926
[ Screaming ]

31:07.433 --> 31:10.236
[ Cawing ]

31:22.748 --> 31:24.650
[ Man ]
Mullah!

31:27.219 --> 31:30.589
[ Man Shouts
In Foreign Language ]

31:34.760 --> 31:36.228
[ Man ]

32:17.803 --> 32:22.041
[ Shouting ]

32:24.710 --> 32:27.446
[ Shouting ]

32:29.015 --> 32:32.384
- Well, they're off.
- You think Betty Blue
could handle the horse?

32:32.451 --> 32:34.720
Horse has a soft spot
for intellectuals.

32:37.456 --> 32:40.492
[ Whistling ]

32:40.559 --> 32:42.528
I guess the horse
didn't kill him.

32:42.594 --> 32:45.231
[ Floorboards Squeak ]
[ Hammer Cocks ]

32:47.066 --> 32:49.068
Easy now.

32:49.135 --> 32:52.438
- I want that horse.
- Why?

32:52.504 --> 32:55.107
- I'm gonna stop that wedding.
- I said we'd discuss it.

32:55.174 --> 32:58.010
You didn't expect me
to believe that.

32:58.077 --> 33:00.612
We're trying
to save American lives here.

33:00.679 --> 33:04.450
I don't care about
American soldiers.
I care about human rights.

33:07.253 --> 33:09.955
You're as guilty
of victimizing women
as they are.

33:10.022 --> 33:12.291
And you would've
left me here to die.

33:12.358 --> 33:14.593
That's why we gave you
the gun:

33:14.660 --> 33:18.064
to protect yourself just in case
something happened to us.

33:18.130 --> 33:20.732
- [ Grey Whistles ]
- Hold tight, Betty Blue!

33:22.434 --> 33:23.669
Now what?

33:23.735 --> 33:24.536
[ Footsteps ]
Look out!

33:29.108 --> 33:30.442
[ Groans ]

33:34.813 --> 33:36.782
Ah, geez.

33:36.848 --> 33:39.551
Think anybody heard that?

33:47.126 --> 33:48.894
[ Gunfire ]

33:48.960 --> 33:50.296
Hell, yeah.

34:12.918 --> 34:17.189
How much farther?
Once we pass the creek bed,
the Taliban will not follow.

34:17.256 --> 34:19.625
They dare not risk a fight
with my tribe's warriors.

34:19.691 --> 34:21.760
Where's this creek bed?

34:23.129 --> 34:26.398
- Betty Blue.
- Got it.

34:31.837 --> 34:34.673
You hear that?
They're coming from the north.

34:36.175 --> 34:38.710
Top, we can't outrun that.

34:38.777 --> 34:42.414
You and Dirt Diver
take care of 'em.
Zar can't run much faster.

34:52.023 --> 34:54.293
Hyah!

35:08.073 --> 35:12.178
[ Shouting ]

35:22.454 --> 35:24.490
[ Men Screaming ]
[ Horses Whinnying ]

35:46.912 --> 35:49.215
[ Arif ]
Here is the creek bed.

36:00.726 --> 36:02.594
[ Horse Whinnies ]

36:24.816 --> 36:27.219
The chief and his son
are grateful to you...

36:27.286 --> 36:31.990
for delivering
this precious cargo safely
during the journey.

36:32.057 --> 36:34.660
You're most welcome.

36:57.683 --> 37:01.720
You mean to make a fool of me?
I assure you, this is not
how she was delivered to me.

37:01.787 --> 37:04.423
When I met her,
she was wearing green.

37:04.490 --> 37:06.458
Lara changed
the girl's clothes.

37:08.827 --> 37:10.862
She is not pure!

37:10.929 --> 37:13.599
She's dressed
like an experienced woman!

37:13.665 --> 37:17.669
Father, I will not marry
this harlot.

37:17.736 --> 37:22.207
There is no truce.
There will be no truce.

37:22.274 --> 37:24.576
You have made this trip
for nothing.

37:25.977 --> 37:28.714
Made the trip for nothing.

37:29.781 --> 37:32.351
You don't s--

37:36.254 --> 37:42.193
Is there any way we can
bring about this truce before
we must leave with our horse--

37:42.260 --> 37:44.863
a Buzkashi championship horse?

37:44.930 --> 37:47.566
Is this horse
not the prize possessions
of Chief Haji?

37:47.633 --> 37:51.437
Chief Haji has given me
the authority,

37:51.503 --> 37:53.805
under certain circumstances,
to dispose of this horse.

37:53.872 --> 37:56.342
And those circumstances?

37:57.943 --> 37:59.945
This signed truce agreement.

38:00.011 --> 38:03.782
A piece of paper may be
important to you Americans,
but it is meaningless to us.

38:03.849 --> 38:07.853
We Pashtuns require
a family bond in order
for a truce to be binding.

38:07.919 --> 38:13.224
Okay. I understand.
Then sadly, we must go...

38:13.291 --> 38:15.361
with our horse.

38:17.262 --> 38:19.531
Wait.

38:19.598 --> 38:22.368
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

38:25.737 --> 38:30.008
The chief's son may not see the
importance of this agreement,
but the chief does.

38:30.075 --> 38:35.046
He will adopt the girl.
She will live among his family
as a treasured daughter!

38:36.715 --> 38:39.351
That's fine.
I think that's--

38:39.418 --> 38:41.520
But-But I have fallen
in love with her...

38:43.955 --> 38:45.891
and she with me.

38:45.957 --> 38:50.195
And we have
exchanged tokens on our trip
which amount to an engagement.

38:50.261 --> 38:52.798
I'll come to collect her
when she's 18.

38:52.864 --> 38:56.835
If I don't return,
then she's free
to marry another.

38:59.371 --> 39:01.540
So be it!

39:04.175 --> 39:06.044
Gave it a shot.

39:11.249 --> 39:14.185
Last chance, Bob.
[ Exhales ]

39:14.252 --> 39:16.087
Tell us what
you know about Reed,

39:16.154 --> 39:19.124
or you'll be charged
as an accessory to a crime.

39:19.190 --> 39:21.427
- There's nothing to tell.
- Well, then
you're a criminal.

39:21.493 --> 39:24.062
No, I'm not a criminal.
Well, then you work
for the government.

39:24.129 --> 39:26.832
If I worked for the government
or could tell you something
about Isaac Reed...

39:26.898 --> 39:29.501
that would get me
out of this jam,
don't you think I'd do it?

39:29.568 --> 39:31.737
I'll tell you
what I think.

39:34.706 --> 39:37.809
I think we're gonna
rough you up, cuff you up...

39:37.876 --> 39:40.646
and make you do
the perp walk downtown,

39:40.712 --> 39:43.915
in leg irons,
for the evening news.

39:46.251 --> 39:48.119
[ Sniffles ]

39:49.921 --> 39:54.392
[ Door Closes ]
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

39:58.396 --> 40:01.467
[ Beeps ]
Hello?

40:01.533 --> 40:03.635
[ Isaac ]
Congratulations, Bob.
You did it.

40:03.702 --> 40:06.538
The money's just been wired
into your account at AeroDyne.

40:06.605 --> 40:09.174
Um, sorry for scaring you,
but I hope you understand...

40:09.240 --> 40:12.243
how crucial it was to vet you
before we took this any further.

40:12.310 --> 40:14.680
You set this up.
That's right.

40:14.746 --> 40:18.149
Oh, and I understand
you were one cool customer.

40:18.216 --> 40:20.752
Didn't give away a single thing.
I'm impressed.

40:20.819 --> 40:23.655
All right.
So what now?
Now you're free to go home.

40:23.722 --> 40:27.358
There's a car waiting outside.
It'll take you to Vegas
for a flight back home.

40:27.425 --> 40:30.762
- No hard feelings.
- No, of course not.

40:30.829 --> 40:34.633
Uh, enjoy your 10%.
See you back
in sunny California.

40:34.700 --> 40:36.802
- [ Beeps ]
- [ Beeps ]

40:39.304 --> 40:42.874
There's no agent of Leon Drake's
description at the F.B.I.'s
Las Vegas field office.

40:42.941 --> 40:44.876
Well, real or fake,
he's working for Reed.

40:44.943 --> 40:46.978
Which makes Reed
a very dangerous man.

40:47.045 --> 40:49.080
Look, I have
his complete trust now.

40:49.147 --> 40:52.383
- You can pull Kim out.
Where is she?
- She's at his house.

40:52.450 --> 40:56.254
- Pull her out.
- We pull her out too quick, it
may arouse Reed's suspicions.

40:56.321 --> 40:59.658
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

40:59.725 --> 41:02.027
[ Beeps ]
It's the police.

41:02.093 --> 41:04.930
- You need
to get out of there now.
- Why?

41:04.996 --> 41:07.599
The police found a body
in the Sierras three weeks ago.

41:07.666 --> 41:09.801
Based on your work,
they I.D.'d it
as Noelle Landers.

41:09.868 --> 41:12.370
She'd been murdered.
Oh, my God.

41:12.437 --> 41:16.842
- Can you leave?
- He's not here.
The baby would be alone.

41:16.908 --> 41:19.645
Look, I'm on my way.
Grab the baby
and get out of there.

41:23.715 --> 41:26.785
[ Inhales ]
I didn't know you were back.

41:26.852 --> 41:30.021
[ Whispering ]
Is everything okay?
Yeah.

41:30.088 --> 41:32.257
Ella just fell asleep.

41:34.492 --> 41:36.562
Come with me.

41:47.405 --> 41:49.741
They're for you.
Why?

41:52.243 --> 41:54.212
What are you doing?

41:55.413 --> 41:57.215
You don't have to
play innocent.

41:57.282 --> 41:59.851
I don't know what impression
I gave you, but--

41:59.918 --> 42:01.820
Kim, you're miserable with Bob.

42:01.887 --> 42:03.922
And him?
[ Chuckles ]

42:03.989 --> 42:06.024
I practically told him
I was falling for you,

42:06.091 --> 42:10.061
and he picked a big paycheck
rather than telling me
to go to hell.

42:10.128 --> 42:12.297
Did you do this
with your previous nanny?

42:12.363 --> 42:15.366
I didn't feel this way
about Noelle.
I feel this way about you.

42:15.433 --> 42:17.368
You didn't come on
to her?

42:17.435 --> 42:19.871
Absolutely not.
Mind if I ask her?

42:27.012 --> 42:28.914
You know,
did I misjudge you?

42:28.980 --> 42:32.718
I'm trying to talk about us,
and all you want to do
is talk about another girl. Why?

